00:13:19,048 --> 00:13:22,260
‐ What do you mean, I'm pushy?
That's not nice‐‐

253
00:13:22,260 --> 00:13:24,846
‐ Well, how can I help you?

254
00:13:24,846 --> 00:13:26,264
‐ Right.

255
00:13:26,264 --> 00:13:29,517
Um, it's like Mikado isn't
himself lately.

256
00:13:29,517 --> 00:13:31,144
‐ Is something wrong with him?

257
00:13:31,144 --> 00:13:33,730
‐ I don't‐‐
I don't really know

258
00:13:33,730 --> 00:13:35,940
how to describe
what's up with him.

259
00:13:35,940 --> 00:13:39,610
It's just he's been acting
kind of strange, is all.

260
00:13:39,610 --> 00:13:41,195
‐ Is he depressed?

261
00:13:41,195 --> 00:13:43,990
‐ No, he seems happier
than ever.

262
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:47,076
I haven't seen him this cheerful
in a really long time.

263
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:53,416
He's like‐‐like he was
when Masaomi was here.

264
00:13:53,416 --> 00:13:56,002
‐ This stalker of hers
is in the Dollars?

265
00:13:56,002 --> 00:13:58,254
‐ I dug around,
and that's what it seems.

266
00:13:58,254 --> 00:14:00,214
I also found out you're in it.

267
00:14:00,214 --> 00:14:01,632
That's why I came here,

268
00:14:01,632 --> 00:14:04,135
to see if you could help
put an end to this.

269
00:14:04,135 --> 00:14:06,304
‐ Yeah, well, I don't know.

270
00:14:06,304 --> 00:14:09,390
You see, I'm not
in the Dollars anymore,

271
00:14:09,390 --> 00:14:11,809
and even when I was,
I didn't know what they were

272
00:14:11,809 --> 00:14:13,311
or who was in it.

273
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:14,562
‐ Oh.

274
00:14:14,562 --> 00:14:15,938
‐ What about the cops?

275
00:14:15,938 --> 00:14:17,356
Did you talk to them?

276
00:14:17,356 --> 00:14:19,400
‐ [whimpers]

277
00:14:22,820 --> 00:14:24,614
Yes, I called them one night

278
00:14:24,614 --> 00:14:26,407
when I couldn't unlock
my front door.

279
00:14:26,407 --> 00:14:28,951
The stalker jammed something
in the keyhole.

280
00:14:28,951 --> 00:14:31,871
‐ They checked the security
footage, every camera.

281
00:14:31,871 --> 00:14:33,706
They said there was
a sketchy‐looking guy

282
00:14:33,706 --> 00:14:37,543
in the hallway outside her door,
but they couldn't see his face.

283
00:14:37,543 --> 00:14:40,213
‐ The police patrolled
the area after that,

284
00:14:40,213 --> 00:14:42,590
but the guy showed up
at my photo shoot.

285
00:14:42,590 --> 00:14:45,426
He left behind a bunch
of bloody pictures of me.

286
00:14:45,426 --> 00:14:46,886
‐ If he knows where you work,

287
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,679
then that narrows
the list of suspects down.

288
00:14:48,679 --> 00:14:50,932
Do you think maybe
he's someone you work with?

289
00:14:50,932 --> 00:14:53,184
‐ It isn't.
The police checked.

290
00:14:53,184 --> 00:14:55,019
They think he might be a fan.

291
00:14:55,019 --> 00:14:57,438
Someone tied with a group
that deals info

292
00:14:57,438 --> 00:14:59,565
about idols online.

293
00:14:59,565 --> 00:15:02,193
‐ I've had scary fans
like that before,

294
00:15:02,193 --> 00:15:03,694
and the police checked
all the ones

295
00:15:03,694 --> 00:15:05,238
who were on my blacklist,

296
00:15:05,238 --> 00:15:07,615
but they all had alibis.

297
00:15:07,615 --> 00:15:09,367
‐ After snooping around,
I found out

298
00:15:09,367 --> 00:15:12,620
the people trading info on Ruri
are in the Dollars.

299
00:15:12,620 --> 00:15:15,123
I tried to register
to check it out,

300
00:15:15,123 --> 00:15:17,166
but the Dollars are such
a tight community

301
00:15:17,166 --> 00:15:20,878
they don't let anyone new in
unless you have an invitation.

302
00:15:20,878 --> 00:15:22,922
‐ Oh, I'm sorry, man.

303
00:15:22,922 --> 00:15:25,842
I don't have the brains to
be a hacker, that's for sure.

304
00:15:25,842 --> 00:15:27,760
And if I only knew more
about the Dollars,

305
00:15:27,760 --> 00:15:30,221
maybe that'd
help you somehow.

306
00:15:30,221 --> 00:15:34,058
There's got to be someone
out there who does, but who?

307
00:15:34,058 --> 00:15:35,518
[cat meows]
Huh?

308
00:15:35,518 --> 00:15:38,479
‐ Hey there, Dokusonmaru.
Are you awake?

309
00:15:38,479 --> 00:15:40,773
Ruri's going to be staying
at my place

310
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:43,067
until the police
catch this maniac.

311
00:15:43,067 --> 00:15:44,735
‐ Huh?
‐ We don't want to leave

312
00:15:44,735 --> 00:15:47,864
Dokusonmaru alone there, because
the stalker might hurt him.

313
00:15:47,864 --> 00:15:50,116
Would you look after him for us?

314
00:15:50,116 --> 00:15:54,871
It'll just be until
the police can catch the guy.

315
00:15:54,871 --> 00:15:59,083
‐ Today we were walking
home from school together.

316
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,877
We said bye and then‐‐

317
00:16:00,877 --> 00:16:03,087
‐ Hey, Anri.

318
00:16:03,087 --> 00:16:04,755
‐ Yes, what?

319
00:16:04,755 --> 00:16:07,008
‐ I know there are things
you don't want to tell me,

320
00:16:07,008 --> 00:16:09,468
and it's okay if you don't.

321
00:16:09,468 --> 00:16:13,347
I doubt I know how to fix
whatever's bugging you,

322
00:16:13,347 --> 00:16:15,933
but no matter what that is
or what you're hiding,

323
00:16:15,933 --> 00:16:19,353
I know I can work things out
so there's a spot for you.

324
00:16:19,353 --> 00:16:20,438
‐ Uh.

325
00:16:20,438 --> 00:16:22,231
‐ You'll see.

326
00:16:22,231 --> 00:16:25,943
I'll fix everything so Masaomi
can come back here too.

327
00:16:25,943 --> 00:16:28,779
All our friends will have
a place here.

328
00:16:28,779 --> 00:16:31,282
Don't worry about a thing, Anri.

329
00:16:31,282 --> 00:16:34,911
‐ He always said Masaomi would
come back to the city someday,

330
00:16:34,911 --> 00:16:38,247
and now he says
he'll fix it so he can.

331
00:16:38,247 --> 00:16:40,458
It's such a weird thing
for him to say.

332
00:16:40,458 --> 00:16:41,918
‐ I think I get it.

333
00:16:41,918 --> 00:16:44,128
Instead of trusting
his friend will come back,

334
00:16:44,128 --> 00:16:46,881
he's putting his faith in his
own power to make it happen.

335
00:16:46,881 --> 00:16:50,051
‐ You're right, that doesn't
sound like Mikado.

336
00:16:50,051 --> 00:16:51,844
‐ Hm.

337
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:54,639
No.

338
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:57,558
‐ What really went down
at that factory?

339
00:16:57,558 --> 00:16:59,477
It was right after that night

340
00:16:59,477 --> 00:17:01,938
the kid showed up
out of the blue.

341
00:17:01,938 --> 00:17:03,606
‐ It's about time...

342
00:17:03,606 --> 00:17:07,193
‐ He certainly didn't act
like he wanted to be friends.

343
00:17:07,193 --> 00:17:08,819
How did you get this address?

344
00:17:08,819 --> 00:17:10,655
‐ Hey, it's okay.
Don't worry.

345
00:17:10,655 --> 00:17:12,657
As long as we're cool,
I won't tell the cops

346
00:17:12,657 --> 00:17:14,242
where you guys live.

347
00:17:14,242 --> 00:17:17,161
I did tell my friends I was
coming here tonight though.

348
00:17:17,161 --> 00:17:19,038
So if I do happen to disappear,

349
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,749
the cops would
definitely show up.

350
00:17:21,749 --> 00:17:24,502
Or maybe a fire will break out.
Who knows?

351
00:17:24,502 --> 00:17:27,672
‐ Huh, you sound like
Izaya Orihara.

352
00:17:27,672 --> 00:17:29,090
‐ [gasps]

353
00:17:29,090 --> 00:17:32,468
I never thought I'd
be compared to that asshole.

354
00:17:32,468 --> 00:17:35,179
‐ Huh, so you do know
Izaya after all.

355
00:17:35,179 --> 00:17:37,765
You guys are totally cut
from the same cloth.

356
00:17:37,765 --> 00:17:41,060
I'd bet you're just like him,
never happy unless you have

357
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:43,104
the world in the palm
of your hand.

358
00:17:43,104 --> 00:17:46,190
Like a couple of
greedy little boys.

359
00:17:46,190 --> 00:17:48,317
You know what I want
in my hand?

360
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:51,696
Celty's, and I'll do anything
to keep her safe.

361
00:17:51,696 --> 00:17:53,239
‐ Stop it, Shinra.

362
00:17:53,239 --> 00:17:56,659
It would be stupid to kill him
over a few vague threats.

363
00:17:56,659 --> 00:17:58,369
‐ Celty.

364
00:17:58,369 --> 00:18:01,038
‐ No reason to get ahead
of ourselves, Doc.

365
00:18:01,038 --> 00:18:04,584
For now, all I want from you
is one email addy.

366
00:18:04,584 --> 00:18:07,169
Give me that,
and I'll leave you alone.

367
00:18:07,169 --> 00:18:09,672
‐ We gave him
that email address,

368
00:18:09,672 --> 00:18:11,382
but we haven't heard
from him since,

369
00:18:11,382 --> 00:18:14,844
and that's got me worried.

370
00:18:14,844 --> 00:18:17,972
Do you know who Mikado
associates with at school?

371
00:18:17,972 --> 00:18:19,432
‐ Huh?

372
00:18:19,432 --> 00:18:22,560
‐ Have you noticed him being
extra chummy with anyone?

373
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:25,271
‐ Let's see,
he's been hanging out a lot

374
00:18:25,271 --> 00:18:27,064
with a younger boy called Aoba.

375
00:18:27,064 --> 00:18:29,275
They're in the same committee
at school.

376
00:18:32,194 --> 00:18:33,613
Thank you for talking to me.

377
00:18:33,613 --> 00:18:35,072
I really appreciate it.

378
00:18:35,072 --> 00:18:37,241
‐ No worries,
but it's gotten pretty late.

379
00:18:37,241 --> 00:18:38,951
If you want,
you can spend the night.

380
00:18:38,951 --> 00:18:41,871
‐ Oh, thank you,
but I couldn't impose on you

381
00:18:41,871 --> 00:18:42,913
like that, really.

382
00:18:42,913 --> 00:18:46,375
[doorbell chimes]
‐ Hmm?

383
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:51,505
[both chuckle]

384
00:18:51,505 --> 00:18:53,716
[meows]

385
00:18:53,716 --> 00:18:56,594
ANRI: I felt a lot better
after talking to them.

386
00:18:56,594 --> 00:18:59,096
It definitely helped
calm me down.

387
00:18:59,096 --> 00:19:02,600
And then I thought
if he really did change,

388
00:19:02,600 --> 00:19:06,437
what could I do to help get him
back to the way he was?

389
00:19:06,437 --> 00:19:08,314
‐ Hey, Saki.

390
00:19:08,314 --> 00:19:10,274
‐ You're going
to Ikebukuro, huh?

391
00:19:10,274 --> 00:19:12,276
‐ Are you psychic?

392
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:13,736
I gave myself a headache

393
00:19:13,736 --> 00:19:15,863
thinking about
how to break it to you.

394
00:19:15,863 --> 00:19:19,450
‐ I knew 'cause you've been
reading all those chat logs.

395
00:19:19,450 --> 00:19:20,951
‐ [sighs]

396
00:19:20,951 --> 00:19:23,746
One of them had a rumor
about there being Blue Squares

397
00:19:23,746 --> 00:19:25,623
in the Dollars.

398
00:19:25,623 --> 00:19:27,958
I'm worried they're planning
on taking over the Dollars,

399
00:19:27,958 --> 00:19:30,378
like how the Yellow Scarves
tried.

400
00:19:30,378 --> 00:19:34,090
I can't ignore that.

401
00:19:34,090 --> 00:19:36,258
‐ Why do you want
to get involved?

402
00:19:36,258 --> 00:19:37,635
Is it for a friend?

403
00:19:37,635 --> 00:19:39,887
‐ Yeah, that's part of it.

404
00:19:39,887 --> 00:19:42,807
There's also a score
I have to settle.

405
00:19:42,807 --> 00:19:46,435
‐ I know it won't do any good
to tell you not to go,

406
00:19:46,435 --> 00:19:47,687
but it's dangerous,

407
00:19:47,687 --> 00:19:49,814
and I don't want you
to get hurt.

408
00:19:49,814 --> 00:19:51,649
‐ Well, that's not fair.

409
00:19:51,649 --> 00:19:54,652
A good girlfriend would
keep that stuff to herself.

410
00:19:54,652 --> 00:19:56,404
‐ I don't care
if it's fair or not.

411
00:19:56,404 --> 00:19:59,198
I'm the one
who has to sit here, waiting.

412
00:19:59,198 --> 00:20:00,741
‐ For me to come back?

413
00:20:00,741 --> 00:20:03,661
‐ For you to crack
those stupid jokes and laugh

414
00:20:03,661 --> 00:20:06,455
and be a dork,
like you used to.

415
00:20:06,455 --> 00:20:09,500
‐ That's definitely not fair.
‐ Huh?

416
00:20:10,876 --> 00:20:14,839
‐ Listen, it's like
I have to go back there,

417
00:20:14,839 --> 00:20:17,591
'cause there's a whole bunch
of people I want you to meet.

418
00:20:17,591 --> 00:20:21,595
They're my friends, and I want
them to meet you, too.

419
00:20:21,595 --> 00:20:23,639
ANRI: It's natural
for this city

420
00:20:23,639 --> 00:20:26,642
and everyone who lives in it
to change.

421
00:20:26,642 --> 00:20:30,521
So why should I want
to stop that from happening?

422
00:20:30,521 --> 00:20:33,733
Do I want things to go back
to the way they were?

423
00:20:33,733 --> 00:20:37,278
‐ Thank God. I'm glad
none of you guys got hurt.

424
00:20:37,278 --> 00:20:40,406
Whatever you do,
try and be careful out there.

425
00:20:41,907 --> 00:20:44,201
‐ They'll be okay,
but check this out.

426
00:20:44,201 --> 00:20:46,537
Ruri Hijiribe's stalker
might be a Dollar.

427
00:20:46,537 --> 00:20:50,624
You hear about that?
‐ Yeah, that's a problem.

428
00:20:50,624 --> 00:20:52,168
We should move on it.

429
00:20:52,168 --> 00:20:55,296
That's the kind of member
the Dollars don't need.

430
00:20:55,296 --> 00:20:57,047
[chime]

431
00:20:57,047 --> 00:20:58,716
GAKI: Nice to meet you.

432
00:20:58,716 --> 00:21:02,052
I look forward to chatting if
anyone ever decides to log on.

433
00:21:02,052 --> 00:21:05,514
Sumiuta‐‐I mean, Saika
sent me an invite,

434
00:21:05,514 --> 00:21:07,099
so here I am.

435
00:21:07,099 --> 00:21:09,727
SHARO: Hello there.
GAKI: Hello.

436
00:21:09,727 --> 00:21:13,105
Nice to meet you.
Do you come to this board often?

437
00:21:13,105 --> 00:21:15,024
SHARO: Nope, I just joined.

438
00:21:15,024 --> 00:21:17,735
I also got an invite
from a friend.

439
00:21:17,735 --> 00:21:19,445
We're the only ones here.

440
00:21:19,445 --> 00:21:21,447
I wonder where the regulars are.

441
00:21:21,447 --> 00:21:22,907
PURE WATER 100%: Hey, guys!

442
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:24,909
I've been lurking this board
up till now.

443
00:21:24,909 --> 00:21:26,744
Do you mind if I join in?

444
00:21:26,744 --> 00:21:29,497
A friend sent me an invite,
but I've never done this before.

445
00:21:29,497 --> 00:21:32,041
Anyway, nice to meet you.

446
00:21:34,251 --> 00:21:37,797
SAKI: Hi, everyone.
Bakyura sent me an invitation.

447
00:21:37,797 --> 00:21:41,258
My name's Saki.
Nice to meet you.

448
00:21:41,258 --> 00:21:44,053
SHARO: Good evening.
PURE WATER 100%: Evening!

449
00:21:44,053 --> 00:21:45,763
GAKI: Oh, my God,
this is turning into

450
00:21:45,763 --> 00:21:48,349
a meet and greet for newbs.

451
00:21:48,349 --> 00:21:49,892
CHROME: Hi there.
Nice to meet you.

452
00:21:49,892 --> 00:21:52,269
Looks like this is where
the party is.

453
00:21:52,269 --> 00:21:54,939
I got an invite, too.
Just like everyone else.

454
00:21:54,939 --> 00:21:56,607
SHARO: Hi, welcome to the board

455
00:21:56,607 --> 00:22:00,110
where everyone comes
to say hello.

456
00:22:00,110 --> 00:22:01,695
BAKYURA: Hello, everyone.

457
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:04,156
Wait, what's up
with all the hellos?

458
00:22:04,156 --> 00:22:06,200
SAKI: Hi, there.

459
00:22:06,200 --> 00:22:08,118
[both chuckle]

460
00:22:08,118 --> 00:22:09,829
‐ Oh.

461
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:12,998
[gasps]

